subject: 2014 Thai coup d'état
object: Successful military and police takeover | Caretaker Prime Minister removed | Yingluck's caretaker government dissolved | 2007 Senate dissolved | 2007 Constitution repealed | Military junta, the NCPO established | Prayut endorsed by Bhumibol as NCPO leader and Prime Minister | 2014 interim constitution by NCPO enacted | 2017 constitution by junta NLA enacted

subject: 2014 Thai coup d'état
object: The coup leaders on television announcing their taking control of the government and suspending the constitution. From left: Adul Saengsingkaew, a police commissioner; Prajin Juntong, an air force chief; Prayut Chan-o-cha, an army chief; Narong Pipathanasai, a navy chief; and Worapong Sanganetra, an armed forces chief deputy.

subject: Belligerents
object: Royal Thai Armed Forces | Royal Thai Police | Supported by | Monarchy of Thailand | Yingluck cabinet
